featured_reviews.review_id:
A Majestic Haven of Worship: Jamia Masjid

Rating:  (5/5)

Nestled in the heart of Kurnool City, Jamia Masjid (Markaz) stands as a testament to architectural grandeur and spiritual significance. With its awe-inspiring domes and towering minarets, this mosque is not just a place of worship; it's a symbol of unity, peace, and community.

The sheer size of Jamia Masjid (Markaz) is awe-inspiring, capable of accommodating over 10,000 worshippers at a time. This capacity is not just a numerical feat; it translates into a truly inclusive space that welcomes people from all walks of life. The vast prayer hall, adorned with intricate calligraphy and beautiful geometric patterns, creates a serene atmosphere conducive to reflection and prayer.

One cannot help but marvel at the meticulous attention to detail in the architecture. The courtyard, surrounded by lush greenery and fountains, provides a tranquil setting for congregants to gather before and after prayers. The expansive prayer hall itself is designed with precision, ensuring that every attendee has a clear line of sight to the imam and the beautiful mihrab.

The facilities at Jamia Masjid (Markaz) are impressive, offering a seamless experience for worshippers. The ablution areas are spacious and well-maintained, ensuring cleanliness and comfort for all.

The spiritual experience at Jamia Masjid (Markaz) is truly unique. The eloquent recitation of the Quran by the imam, combined with the harmonious echoes of congregational prayers, creates a profound sense of unity and devotion. The mosque's commitment to fostering a sense of community is evident in its various programs, including educational classes, community outreach initiatives, and cultural events.

Security and organization are top-notch at Jamia Masjid (Markaz). Despite the large capacity, the mosque efficiently manages the flow of worshippers, ensuring a smooth and peaceful experience for all. The dedicated staff and volunteers contribute to the welcoming atmosphere, always ready to assist and guide visitors.

In conclusion, Jamia Masjid (Markaz) is more than just a place of worship; it's a marvel of architecture, a hub of spirituality, and a beacon of inclusivity. Whether you're a devout worshipper or a curious visitor, the mosque offers an enriching and harmonious experience that transcends cultural and religious boundaries. Visiting Jamia Masjid (Markaz) is not just a journey of faith; it's a journey of the soul.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Dargah Hazrat Syed Shah Abdul Lateef Laubali Quadri Al Hamavi RA is located in Kurnool. Hazrat Laubali (Rh) is the direct descendant of Ghouse Pak of Baghdad. It is also called as "Second Baghdad". Hazrat Laubali  took his auspicious birth in the 15th descent from Ghousul Azam. His ancestral lineage or genealogy is  furnished below:

(1)  SYED SHAH LATEEF LAUBALI son of
(2)  SYED SHAH TAHER -AL- HAMVI, son of
(3)  SYED ZAHID-AL-HAMVI, son of
(4)  SYED HASHIM-AL-HAMVI, son of
(5)  SYED QUTBUDDIN MUHAMMAD-AL-HAMVI, son of
(6)  SYED SHABBUDDIN AHMED-AL- HAMVI, son of,
(7)  SYED BADRUDDIN HASSAN -AL-HAMVI, son of,
(8)  SYED ALAUDDIN ALI -AL- HAMVI, son of
(9)  SYED SHAMSHUDDIN MOHAMMED, son of
(10) SYED SAIFUDDIN YAHYA -AL- HAMVI, son of
(11) SYED ZAHEERUDDIN AHMED -AL- BAGDADI, son of
(12) SYED SHAMSHUDDIN ABU NASR -AL- BAGDADI, son of
(13) SYED IMADUDDIN ABU SALEH NASR -AL- BAGDADI, son of
(14) SYED TAJUDDIN ABU BAKR ABDUR RAZACK -AL- BAGDADI, son of
(15) SYED UL MASHOOQAIN  SYEDANA  SHAIKH  ABDUL  QADIR   JEELANI.
From Hazarath Syed-al-Hamavi, Hazarath Lateef Laubali  had drawn immense spiritual grace and benefit which he faithfully transferred to his disciples and they drew benefits according to their desires.
